    "4: Results of User Study.",
    "10 -strong agreement, 5neutral, 0 -strong disagreement.",
    "We use semantic in two categories of meaning.",
    "When it is used for \"semantic information\", it refers to the semantics of information like comments and variable names.",
    "When it is used for \"function/code semantics\", it refers to the behaviors of the function/code.Network and Distributed System Security (NDSS) Symposium 26 February -1 March 2024, San Diego, CA, USA ISBN 1-891562-93-2 https://dx.doi.org/10.14722/ndss.2024.24401 www.ndss-symposium.org We use \"fidelity\" to describe how close the decompiler output is to the actual semantics of the decompiled binary."
